    <h2>1. Parties</h2>
    <p><strong>Provider:</strong> {{ site.legal.entityName }}, CNPJ {{ t.footer.cnpjValue }}. <strong>Client:</strong> the individual or legal entity that submits the request. A request is considered accepted upon our written confirmation (WhatsApp, Telegram or email).</p>

    <h2>2. Service</h2>
    <p>Private passenger transfer on an agreed route — within Brazil and between Mercosur countries. The service includes driver, fuel, tolls and parking on the route.</p>

    <h2>3. Booking and confirmation</h2>
    <p>Requests are submitted via the site, WhatsApp, Telegram or email. After the route, time and conditions are agreed, we send a written confirmation with the price and payment details. The booking is in force from our confirmation, not from the request.</p>

    <h2>4. Price and payment</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The price is locked before departure and does not change on the road, unless the route is changed at the client's request.</li>
      <li>Accepted: Pix, bank transfer, cash, card. For recurring partners and companies — invoice with deferred payment.</li>
      <li>For companies we issue an NF-e (electronic invoice) within 5 business days after the service.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Cancellations and changes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>More than 24 hours before departure — cancellation and change with no fee.</li>
      <li>24–6 hours — partial preparation fee retained (up to 30 % of the price).</li>
      <li>Less than 6 hours or no-show — full price retained.</li>
      <li>If we cancel (vehicle failure, driver illness without backup) — full refund.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Delays and waiting</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>At airports: free wait of 60 minutes after landing; 90 minutes for international flights. After that — at the agreed waiting rate.</li>
      <li>At addresses: free wait of 15 minutes. After that — at the waiting rate.</li>
      <li>Flight delays are monitored automatically; the pickup time adjusts at no extra cost.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Passengers, luggage, animals</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Passenger and luggage counts are confirmed in advance and may not exceed the capacity of the selected vehicle class.</li>
      <li>Children under 10 travel in an appropriate car seat / booster (provided on request).</li>
      <li>Pets — only with prior notice, in a carrier or on a leash, with a possible cleaning surcharge.</li>
      <li>Bulky or fragile luggage (bikes, surfboards, instruments) — declared at booking.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Passenger conduct</h2>
    <p>Prohibited: smoking (including vaping), consuming alcohol or other substances in the vehicle, leaving trash. The driver may terminate the trip for aggressive behaviour, safety risk or law violation; in that case the payment is not refunded.</p>

    <h2>9. Delays, force majeure</h2>
    <p>We are not liable for delays caused by circumstances beyond our control: traffic, accidents en route, weather, strikes, road closures, government actions, border queues. In such cases we communicate promptly and propose an alternative plan.</p>

    <h2>10. Liability</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The vehicle carries the mandatory DPVAT insurance and voluntary passenger insurance.</li>
      <li>We are liable for damage caused by our fault to the extent of applicable law.</li>
      <li>We are not liable for missed connections, flights or events when the delay is not our fault.</li>
      <li>The client is responsible for documents (passports, visas) for international routes.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>11. Complaints</h2>
    <p>Complaints to <a href="mailto:{{ site.contacts.email }}">{{ site.contacts.email }}</a>. Review period — up to 10 business days. Consumer disputes are governed by the Brazilian Consumer Defence Code (CDC).</p>

    <h2>12. Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>We may amend these terms. The version in force at the time of booking confirmation applies.</p>

    <h2>13. Governing law</h2>
    <p>Governing law — Federal Republic of Brazil. Jurisdiction: courts of {{ site.legal.city }}, unless the CDC provides otherwise.</p>

